11. Do not use doxing: Doxing involves publicly sharing someone's personal information without their consent. Avoid using doxing to harass or intimidate others.

12. Do not use malware: Using malware to harm others online is not acceptable. Avoid using malware to harm others.

13. Do not use hacking: Hacking is the unauthorized access to someone's computer or network. Avoid using hacking to harm others online.

14. Do not use phishing: Phishing involves tricking someone into giving away their personal information. Avoid using phishing to harm others online.

15. Do not use spam: Spam is unsolicited messages sent to a large number of people. Avoid using spam to harass or intimidate others.

